Description:
## Description

We're doing a query to update all carts as pushed_to_kafka=true. But there seems to not be a where condition on this. This obviously seems incorrect: 

* There can be a race condition where a new cart was added, between the last read and the update
* A better approach will be update by created timestamp or ids of carts pushed, to ensure we only update the right ones.

The query is also super inefficient because it's updating all 70k rows right now, even a query of where pushed_to_kafka=false, will reduce that a lot, cause there's a index.

```
